00:15.306 --> 00:17.517
[Poppy]  ♪ Put your hair up in the air ♪

00:17.600 --> 00:19.352
♪ Live it up ♪

00:19.436 --> 00:21.396
♪ Every day you wake up singing ♪

00:21.479 --> 00:23.356
♪  Turn it up ♪

00:23.440 --> 00:25.275
♪ The party's just beginning ♪

00:25.358 --> 00:27.235
♪ All together you and me ♪

00:27.318 --> 00:29.195
♪ Hair in the air, we're a family ♪

00:29.279 --> 00:31.281
♪ We got everything we need ♪

00:31.364 --> 00:33.366
♪ Hair in the air
'Cause we're proud to be ♪

00:33.450 --> 00:35.410
♪ Celebrating who we are ♪

00:35.493 --> 00:37.287
♪ Yeah, we made it through the dark ♪

00:37.370 --> 00:39.205
♪ Harmony is everywhere ♪

00:39.289 --> 00:41.291
♪ Put your hair up in the air ♪

00:41.374 --> 00:43.168
♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah ♪

00:43.251 --> 00:45.420
♪  Put your hair up in the air ♪

00:46.045 --> 00:48.673
[bright music]

00:48.757 --> 00:52.010
[Biggie] The ghost followed
the Troll inside her home.

00:52.093 --> 00:54.888
She turned, heart in her throat.

00:54.971 --> 00:56.473
-[gasps]
-Their eyes locked.

00:56.556 --> 00:59.893
-Ah!
-This was the end...

00:59.976 --> 01:01.770
of loneliness!

01:01.853 --> 01:02.896
[all] Aw!

01:02.979 --> 01:08.318
The two embraced, a hug for the ages,
and lived happily ever after.

01:08.401 --> 01:11.905
-[cheering]
-What a twist.

01:11.988 --> 01:15.950
Yeah, another ghost story where
the ghost and the Troll fall in love.

01:16.034 --> 01:17.327
Shocker.

01:17.410 --> 01:20.246
Biggie, thrilling as always.

01:20.330 --> 01:21.748
Does anyone else have a tale?

01:21.831 --> 01:23.917
Perhaps our special guest?

01:24.000 --> 01:25.335
Well, I do.

01:25.418 --> 01:29.422
But Troll scary stories are
way different than Bergen ones.

01:29.506 --> 01:31.674
-Tell it!
-[all chanting] Tell it, tell it!

01:31.758 --> 01:33.802
Well, okay!

01:33.885 --> 01:34.886
[all gasp]

01:34.969 --> 01:38.306
It was a night just like this.

01:38.389 --> 01:42.811
Two teens wanted
the time of their lives, and they got it.

01:42.894 --> 01:44.687
The guy said, "Hey, Janet.

01:44.771 --> 01:47.357
Thanks for coming with me
to Hold Hands Point."

01:47.440 --> 01:48.775
But Janet was all like,

01:48.858 --> 01:51.277
"Wait, Derrick, I hear something.

01:51.361 --> 01:53.446
-What if it's the Greygon monster?"
-[growls]

01:53.530 --> 01:57.117
[scoffs] " Janet, it's just the wind.

01:57.200 --> 02:00.328
-Now...
-[spritzing]

02:00.411 --> 02:02.288
...shall we? Shah."

02:02.372 --> 02:05.667
[gasps, sighs]  "Uh-huh."
"I feel so close to you."

02:05.750 --> 02:06.918
[roaring]

02:07.001 --> 02:08.919
[screams]  No!

02:09.002 --> 02:12.048
But Janet and Derrick,
they were okay, right?

02:12.132 --> 02:14.551
Uh-huh, they were found the next day...

02:14.634 --> 02:15.760
in pieces!

02:15.844 --> 02:19.013
[all screaming]

02:19.097 --> 02:20.140
[cowering]

02:20.223 --> 02:22.559
[Troll] No, no, no, no.
No, no, no, no, no! No, no!

02:22.642 --> 02:24.602
Guys? Guys?

02:24.686 --> 02:27.355
Ah, I think they liked it.

02:27.438 --> 02:29.774
Watermelon? [chomps]

02:29.858 --> 02:32.277
[Poppy] Ugh. I feel awful.

02:32.360 --> 02:36.406
But how was I to know Bridget's
scary story would be so... scary?

02:36.489 --> 02:39.367
I just hope this'll help everyone relax.

02:39.450 --> 02:41.995
Sure, the answer
to all of life's problems--

02:42.078 --> 02:43.913
cheese Danish.

02:43.997 --> 02:46.791
You know, Branch,
your sarcasm really bugs me.

02:46.875 --> 02:49.544
[chomps] But now I'm better!

02:49.627 --> 02:52.213
[Chenille screams]

02:52.297 --> 02:53.965
Chenille, what's wrong?

02:54.048 --> 02:57.468
The Greygon... it got Satin.

02:57.552 --> 03:00.513
[both screaming]

03:02.223 --> 03:03.766
[both] Got you!

03:03.850 --> 03:04.934
[laughter]

03:05.018 --> 03:08.104
Got you, Branch! Got you, Poppy!

03:08.187 --> 03:10.982
[chuckling] Classic.

03:11.065 --> 03:14.986
Got to say, I was afraid
you all would never get over last night.

03:15.069 --> 03:18.489
Yeah, we're all back to normal...
except Biggie.

03:18.573 --> 03:20.783
He spent all night
Greygon-proofing his pod.

03:20.867 --> 03:21.701
See?

03:21.784 --> 03:25.204
[dramatic music]

03:25.288 --> 03:27.123
[Poppy] Look at all these defenses.

03:27.206 --> 03:28.458
Ugh, this is not good.

03:28.541 --> 03:31.878
I know.
These boards couldn't stop a stiff breeze.

03:31.961 --> 03:33.421
[chuckles] Amateur hour.

03:34.505 --> 03:36.049
[Biggie yelps]

03:36.132 --> 03:37.467
[drill whirring]

03:38.551 --> 03:40.762
Hmm, you look like Poppy.

03:40.845 --> 03:42.847
-[drill whirring]
-[sniffing]

03:42.931 --> 03:45.141
And you smell like Poppy.

03:45.225 --> 03:48.186
But how do I know
you're not the Greygon tricking me?

03:48.269 --> 03:50.980
Tell me things
only the real Poppy would know,

03:51.064 --> 03:55.109
like my favorite thing,
my middle name, and my secret password.

03:55.193 --> 03:58.238
Hugs, Hugs, and open sesame hugs.

03:58.321 --> 03:59.364
[Branch grunts]

04:01.407 --> 04:02.408
Sorry.

04:02.492 --> 04:05.453
You can't be too careful
with a Greygon out and about.

04:05.536 --> 04:10.416
That's why Mr. Dinkles and I are staying
locked up in here until the day we die.

04:10.500 --> 04:13.336
-Meep.
-You did too agree to this...

04:13.419 --> 04:15.255
while you were sleeping.

04:15.338 --> 04:16.839
-[bell ringing]
-[shrieks]

04:18.173 --> 04:19.884
Ha-ha-ha, tea, anyone?

04:19.968 --> 04:23.179
[ceramic rattling]

04:23.263 --> 04:26.474
Oh, I guess my nerves
are still a little bit shaky.

04:26.557 --> 04:29.811
-I'll pour you another cup.
-You know what? I'm good.

04:29.894 --> 04:33.273
Biggie, seriously, come outside with me.
You're perfectly safe.

04:33.356 --> 04:34.524
[Branch grunts]

04:36.192 --> 04:38.611
Hmm, it does seem pretty calm.

04:38.695 --> 04:39.529
[shrieks]

04:39.612 --> 04:40.947
[hammering]

04:41.030 --> 04:42.615
It's just the wind!

04:42.699 --> 04:45.034
[Biggie] That's exactly
what Janet and Derrick thought!

04:45.660 --> 04:48.621
Biggie, please, you got to come out!

04:48.705 --> 04:51.040
-No, I don't.
-Poppy, it's okay.

04:51.124 --> 04:53.793
When push comes to shove,
he'll overcome his fear.

04:53.876 --> 04:56.254
-No, I won't.
-See, Branch?

04:56.337 --> 04:58.423
[sighs] I got to do something about this.

05:00.008 --> 05:02.635
When you're ready to get serious
about home security,

05:02.719 --> 05:07.015
here's the info
for my electrified-fence guy--me.

05:09.851 --> 05:13.104
What? You said you needed
to borrow a few things!

05:13.187 --> 05:15.398
That's because I misled you!

05:16.024 --> 05:19.152
I'm building an exact replica
of the Greygon monster

05:19.235 --> 05:22.155
to trick Biggie
into getting over his fear. See?

05:22.238 --> 05:23.323
[growls]

05:23.406 --> 05:24.240
[grunts]

05:24.324 --> 05:27.285
[imitating Biggie]
I'm over my fear, thanks to you, Poppy.

05:27.368 --> 05:30.163
[imitating Guy Diamond]
Brilliant strategy, Poppy.

05:30.246 --> 05:32.165
-[imitating Smidge] Oh, my Guh!
-What?

05:32.248 --> 05:33.750
How did this become the plan?

05:33.833 --> 05:35.585
And it's more like...
[imitating Smidge] Oh, my Guh.

05:35.668 --> 05:38.671
When I was a kid, I was afraid
there was a monster in my closet.

05:38.755 --> 05:40.965
But instead of trying
to prove it wasn't real,

05:41.049 --> 05:44.177
my dad "fought" the monster
and chased it off.

05:44.260 --> 05:46.012
After that, I slept like a baby.

05:46.095 --> 05:49.557
So how do we get started, builder man?

05:49.640 --> 05:52.393
First things first,
we don't do this at all.

05:52.477 --> 05:53.770
It's a horrible idea!

05:53.853 --> 05:57.523
Oh, well. [sighs]
Guess I'll build it on my own, then.

05:57.607 --> 06:00.985
Maybe frosting would work as glue.

06:01.069 --> 06:02.862
Three, two...

06:02.945 --> 06:05.448
Frosting? A solvent-based adhesive?

06:05.531 --> 06:06.866
You need polymers, Poppy.

06:06.949 --> 06:09.952
-Polymers!
-Right, right. So like icing?

06:10.036 --> 06:12.413
[grunting] Just--just let me do it.

06:12.497 --> 06:14.499
[chuckles] Icing? Really?

06:14.582 --> 06:17.585
[upbeat music]

06:17.668 --> 06:21.339
♪ ♪

06:21.422 --> 06:22.715
[chomps]

06:22.799 --> 06:25.676
♪ ♪

06:25.760 --> 06:28.429
[grunts] Ha! Showed you.

06:28.513 --> 06:29.972
[slurping]

06:30.056 --> 06:31.641
You sure did!

06:32.558 --> 06:36.395
All right, when the Greygon monster comes,
just act scared.

06:36.479 --> 06:38.523
[all scream]

06:38.606 --> 06:39.732
Save some for the show.

06:41.025 --> 06:43.236
[Biggie shrieks] Just a second!

06:43.319 --> 06:44.445
[drill whirring]

06:44.529 --> 06:48.116
-Hmm, how do I know--
-Hugs, Hugs, open sesame hugs.

06:48.199 --> 06:50.409
It's me, Biggie,
I just came to check in on you.

06:50.493 --> 06:51.452
[rumbling]

06:51.536 --> 06:54.247
Oh, no, the Greygon monster!

06:54.330 --> 06:55.915
It is real!

06:57.208 --> 06:59.627
This is terrifying!

06:59.710 --> 07:01.629
[roaring]

07:01.712 --> 07:03.256
[all screaming]

07:03.339 --> 07:06.467
Biggie was right, but none of us listened!

07:06.551 --> 07:08.678
Such folly! [whimpering]

07:08.761 --> 07:11.013
I knew we should've had rehearsals.

07:12.807 --> 07:14.350
[all screaming]

07:14.434 --> 07:16.352
-[laughter]
-[Guy Diamond] I'm running away!

07:17.061 --> 07:18.938
Poppy, get in here!

07:19.021 --> 07:20.148
Don't worry, Biggie.

07:20.231 --> 07:23.651
This Greygon is about to be Grey-gone.

07:23.734 --> 07:25.653
-Ugh, puns?
-[cracks knuckles]

07:25.736 --> 07:29.282
[female chorus]  ♪ We are the winners
You're just beginners ♪

07:29.365 --> 07:32.034
♪ If you're not with us
You are against... ♪

07:32.118 --> 07:34.662
Oh-oh, this ends now.

07:34.745 --> 07:36.080
[chorus]  ♪ Or ever top us... ♪

07:36.164 --> 07:36.998
Whoa, whoa!

07:37.081 --> 07:38.416
I can't watch!

07:38.499 --> 07:40.168
-[chorus]  ♪ Until the end ♪
-Ha-ha!

07:40.251 --> 07:41.461
[chorus]  ♪ We will defend ♪

07:41.544 --> 07:42.420
♪ Na na na na ♪

07:42.503 --> 07:44.005
-♪ Na na na na na ♪
-Yahh!

07:44.088 --> 07:47.091
[chorus]  ♪ We will defend, na na na na ♪

07:47.175 --> 07:48.426
Oh, my.

07:48.509 --> 07:50.303
-[chorus]  ♪ Na na na na ♪
-[grunts]

07:50.386 --> 07:53.055
[chorus]  ♪ Na na na na na na
We will defend, hey, hey ♪

07:53.139 --> 07:55.558
-♪ Na na na na na na, until the end ♪
-[gasps]

07:57.560 --> 07:59.854
Now, this is how you use frosting.

08:00.730 --> 08:03.065
-[gasps]
-[chorus]  ♪ Until the end ♪

08:03.149 --> 08:04.692
♪ We will defend ♪

08:04.775 --> 08:08.070
[roaring]

08:10.281 --> 08:11.949
[eerie music]

08:12.033 --> 08:14.327
[snarling]

08:16.996 --> 08:18.331
You did it!

08:18.414 --> 08:21.000
He won't be bothering you anymore.

08:22.210 --> 08:23.503
[bell ringing]

08:23.586 --> 08:25.963
Who'd like a spot of victory tea?

08:26.047 --> 08:28.591
♪ ♪

08:28.674 --> 08:32.886
Hey, hey, looks like someone's
not shaking anymore!

08:32.970 --> 08:35.556
True, but he is still spilling tea
everywhere.

08:35.640 --> 08:38.976
Ooh, now who'd like some victory soup?

08:39.059 --> 08:41.354
-Please don't.
-Oh, right.

08:41.437 --> 08:46.025
Anyway, to Poppy,
for getting rid of the Greygon for good!

08:46.108 --> 08:47.610
[creature roaring]

08:51.697 --> 08:54.700
[gasps] An actual Greygon?

08:54.784 --> 08:56.285
But they're not real!

08:56.369 --> 08:58.746
Uh, I don't remember
Bridget ever saying that.

08:58.829 --> 08:59.872
Another Greygon?

08:59.956 --> 09:03.793
[roaring]

09:03.876 --> 09:05.002
[gasps]

09:05.086 --> 09:07.046
[all screaming]

09:07.964 --> 09:10.174
It's even bigger than the first!

09:10.258 --> 09:13.302
The bigger they are,
the harder they fall...

09:13.386 --> 09:15.096
if you can get them to fall...

09:15.763 --> 09:17.098
...which I can.

09:17.181 --> 09:19.183
[yelling]

09:20.851 --> 09:22.562
[roars]

09:22.645 --> 09:24.438
Ahh! Ugh!

09:25.064 --> 09:26.899
You guys are gonna die.

09:26.983 --> 09:29.026
Run, run, run, run, run!

09:29.110 --> 09:32.029
[suspenseful music]

09:32.113 --> 09:35.032
♪ ♪

09:35.116 --> 09:35.992
[roaring]

09:36.075 --> 09:39.912
Poppy, please, just fight him off
like you did before.

09:39.996 --> 09:43.541
Uh, yeah, funny thing about that.

09:43.624 --> 09:47.169
[chuckles] Branch and I staged
the whole thing to get you over your fear.

09:47.253 --> 09:48.504
-[chuckles]
-You what?

09:48.588 --> 09:51.048
Clearly I didn't do the best job.

09:51.132 --> 09:53.843
I'm sorry, Biggie.
I thought I was helping you.

09:53.926 --> 09:56.387
But right now I need you to help me fight.

09:56.470 --> 09:57.805
We can use the Greygon suit!

09:57.888 --> 10:01.392
-Come on!
-I can't. I'm a hugger, not a fighter.

10:02.101 --> 10:03.603
[Poppy screams]

10:03.686 --> 10:04.562
No!

10:04.645 --> 10:07.231
-[screaming]
-Poppy!

10:07.315 --> 10:12.028
♪ ♪

10:12.111 --> 10:14.238
I'm coming, Poppy.

10:14.322 --> 10:16.782
You want a piece of me? Bring it on!

10:16.866 --> 10:19.160
-[roars]
-[screams]

10:19.243 --> 10:23.748
♪ ♪

10:23.831 --> 10:27.084
[growling]

10:27.168 --> 10:28.169
Biggie?

10:28.252 --> 10:31.088
Mr. Greygon, this is the end...

10:31.172 --> 10:33.424
of your loneliness.

10:33.507 --> 10:35.509
Commence flirtatious whistling!

10:36.761 --> 10:38.763
[wolf-whistles]

10:38.846 --> 10:40.514
[purring]

10:40.598 --> 10:42.600
Initiate affirmative wink!

10:42.683 --> 10:45.519
[romantic Latin guitar music]

10:45.603 --> 10:48.522
It's working!
Keep it up, Biggie! Whoo-hoo!

10:48.606 --> 10:52.234
♪ ♪

10:52.318 --> 10:53.527
[screams]

10:53.611 --> 10:55.112
Ugh!

10:55.196 --> 10:57.448
Well, well, well, the plot thickens.

10:57.531 --> 11:04.538
♪ ♪

11:08.250 --> 11:11.379
Now deploy hug for the ages!

11:11.462 --> 11:14.715
♪ ♪

11:14.799 --> 11:17.301
Doesn't it feel good to be held?

11:17.385 --> 11:18.260
Ooh.

11:18.344 --> 11:25.351
♪ ♪

11:25.434 --> 11:28.312
Biggie, buddy boy, I'm proud of you.

11:28.396 --> 11:31.023
When push came to shove,
you overcame your fear.

11:31.107 --> 11:32.983
I guess I did, didn't I?

11:33.067 --> 11:34.819
All's well that ends well.

11:34.902 --> 11:38.072
And this ended very well for that Greygon.

11:38.155 --> 11:40.866
Ah, I love happy endings.

11:40.950 --> 11:42.118
Don't you?

11:42.201 --> 11:43.577
[Branch groans]

11:44.703 --> 11:47.623
[calm music]

11:47.706 --> 11:53.671
♪ ♪

11:53.754 --> 11:56.257
Mr. Dinkles, please snap out of it.

11:56.340 --> 11:58.300
This is what I mean.

11:58.384 --> 12:01.470
Ever since Mr. Dinkles's friends
turned to butterflies,

12:01.554 --> 12:04.932
he's been in a pit of low self-esteem.

12:05.015 --> 12:06.767
-Meep.
-See?

12:06.851 --> 12:08.269
He's a mess!

12:08.352 --> 12:09.728
[sobbing]

12:09.812 --> 12:11.689
-Oh, Mr. Dinkles.
-You're right, Biggie.

12:11.772 --> 12:13.566
I've never heard him so out of sorts.

12:13.649 --> 12:15.443
You guys got all that from "meep"?

12:15.526 --> 12:18.654
-You didn't?
-He meeped it pretty clearly, Branch.

12:20.030 --> 12:22.158
Look, just give Dinkles
some space, Biggie.

12:22.241 --> 12:25.119
-He'll bounce back eventually.
-Ooh, you're right, Branch.

12:25.202 --> 12:27.997
I just need to find a way to boost
Mr. Dinkles's confidence

12:28.080 --> 12:32.501
and make him turn back
to the man about town we know and love.

12:32.585 --> 12:34.503
-Wait, that's the opposite of what I--
-I agree!

12:34.587 --> 12:36.213
Ah, great idea, Branch.

12:36.297 --> 12:38.174
And actually, Gristle was just telling me

12:38.257 --> 12:41.969
about something that could be
the perfect way to bring back his swagger.

12:42.052 --> 12:44.054
[birds chirping]

12:44.138 --> 12:45.764
[upbeat music]

12:45.848 --> 12:47.266
-[chomps]
-Ow!

12:47.349 --> 12:50.352
The West Bergen Town Pet Show.

12:50.436 --> 12:53.314
A contest that answers
the question on all owners' minds--

12:53.397 --> 12:56.692
is my pet fancier than everyone else's?

12:56.775 --> 12:58.360
Wow!

12:58.444 --> 12:59.487
Aw!

12:59.570 --> 13:01.238
This is so wrong.

13:01.322 --> 13:06.410
The winning pet is crowned "Best In Show"
and takes home the Golden Gristle,

13:06.494 --> 13:10.414
named after my father, who practically
gave his right arm for this event.

13:10.498 --> 13:11.749
Also literally.

13:11.832 --> 13:14.502
Oh, my, the Golden Gristle.

13:14.585 --> 13:17.922
Getting one of those would put the pep
in your step, eh, Mr. Dinkles?

13:18.005 --> 13:18.839
Meep.

13:18.923 --> 13:20.633
No, I don't think you can win.

13:20.716 --> 13:23.427
-I know you can win.
-Win?

13:23.511 --> 13:26.847
[coughs, chuckles]
A mutt like that can't win.

13:26.931 --> 13:31.852
Where's his highfalutin hairstyle,
his holier-than-thou gaze?

13:31.936 --> 13:35.648
Well, well, well, classic Groth,
always looking down on others.

13:35.731 --> 13:37.525
But who are you to judge, Groth?

13:37.608 --> 13:39.193
Who are you to judge?

13:39.276 --> 13:40.569
I'm the judge.

13:40.653 --> 13:43.447
Ah. I'll be quiet, then.

13:43.531 --> 13:46.200
[scoffs]
Does this worm even have a talent?

13:46.283 --> 13:49.495
Course he does. Let's show 'em, Mr. D!

13:49.578 --> 13:52.665
A-five, six, seven, eight,
and a-step and a-step,

13:52.748 --> 13:55.459
and up and down and turn, turn...

13:56.377 --> 13:59.630
-[scatting]
-[laughter]

13:59.713 --> 14:03.384
[scoffs] That's not a talent.
These are talents.

14:04.343 --> 14:05.261
[barks]

14:05.344 --> 14:08.806
[upbeat music]

14:08.889 --> 14:11.809
[playing soft melody]

14:11.892 --> 14:13.811
[whispering] Wow!

14:13.894 --> 14:18.315
Oh, yeah. That routine won Num-nums
"Best In Show" last year.

14:18.399 --> 14:20.985
But good luck with your dance.

14:21.068 --> 14:22.486
[laughter]

14:22.570 --> 14:25.281
Just to be clear--we were laughing at you,
not with you.

14:25.364 --> 14:26.699
[laughing]

14:26.782 --> 14:28.075
[indistinct chatter]

14:28.158 --> 14:30.494
Guys, can I be honest?

14:30.578 --> 14:32.705
Those other pets were really talented,

14:32.788 --> 14:35.082
and I'm not sure
how Mr. Dinkles can compete.

14:35.165 --> 14:36.917
You're amazing!

14:37.001 --> 14:38.669
[whispering] No, really, we need help.

14:38.752 --> 14:42.256
Well, you know, Biggie, Mr. Dinkles
doesn't have to compete.

14:42.339 --> 14:44.884
[gasps] You mean back out?

14:44.967 --> 14:46.719
He'd think I don't believe in him.

14:46.802 --> 14:50.890
I believe in you! No. Dinkles will win.

14:50.973 --> 14:54.602
Yeah, he'll win, Branch.
We just need to find him a new talent.

14:54.685 --> 14:57.313
[Nangus] Someone say a pet needs a talent?

14:57.396 --> 15:01.901
Then you, my little fuzz nuggets,
have come to the right guy.

15:01.984 --> 15:03.527
Uh, we didn't come to you.

15:03.611 --> 15:06.488
You were just weirdly standing
in the shadows.

15:06.572 --> 15:09.116
Or was I?

15:09.199 --> 15:10.117
No, I was.

15:10.200 --> 15:14.788
Hey, you're, uh, Nangus,
the Bergen dungeon master, right?

15:14.872 --> 15:19.835
Well, that's my nine to five.
But from five to nine, I train pets!

15:19.919 --> 15:21.045
[hoots]

15:22.713 --> 15:24.173
[Poppy] Whoa!

15:24.256 --> 15:27.343
Aw, well, hello, there, birdie.

15:27.426 --> 15:28.260
Ew.

15:28.344 --> 15:31.513
This guy's pretty full of himself,
even for a bird.

15:31.597 --> 15:34.099
You would be, too, if you won
the West Bergen Pet Show

15:34.183 --> 15:36.602
so many times,
they stopped letting you enter.

15:36.685 --> 15:38.812
♪ ♪

15:38.896 --> 15:40.397
[hoots]

15:40.481 --> 15:42.691
♪ ♪

15:42.775 --> 15:45.778
-Oh!
-[train whistle blows]

15:45.861 --> 15:48.614
And if you like,
I can train your petite pal there too.

15:48.697 --> 15:51.408
Wha--Mr. Dinkles doesn't need training.

15:52.242 --> 15:54.411
Yes, absolutely, train him.

15:54.495 --> 15:56.205
[laid-back music]

15:56.288 --> 15:58.123
Let's start with something simple.

15:58.207 --> 15:59.500
Jump through the hoop.

16:00.876 --> 16:03.921
-Ooh.
-I see the problem now.

16:04.004 --> 16:07.591
He has no confidence.

16:07.675 --> 16:11.679
Mr. Dinkles, to be a winner,
you must believe you're a winner.

16:12.930 --> 16:18.227
[Nangus]  This is the universe,
and at the center of it is you!

16:18.310 --> 16:23.357
-Because you can do anything!
-Doesn't this seem a little brainwashy?

16:23.440 --> 16:25.567
Let the man work.

16:25.651 --> 16:27.152
[Nangus]  ...has ever known!

16:27.236 --> 16:31.490
There are no obstacles to your success!

16:31.573 --> 16:35.536
You are as powerful
as a lion riding a shark

16:35.619 --> 16:39.790
into a volcano of awesome!

16:39.873 --> 16:42.001
You are the best!

16:42.084 --> 16:44.294
You are the best!

16:44.378 --> 16:46.672
You are the best!

16:46.755 --> 16:49.758
You are the best!

16:52.011 --> 16:54.888
Dinkles' training is complete.

16:54.972 --> 16:56.306
Behold.

16:56.390 --> 16:57.474
[gong sounds]

16:57.558 --> 17:01.103
[energetic music]

17:01.186 --> 17:02.229
Oh!

17:02.312 --> 17:06.442
♪ ♪

17:06.525 --> 17:07.483
[gasps]

17:07.568 --> 17:10.570
♪ ♪

17:10.654 --> 17:12.448
-[Biggie] Ohhh...
-Meep.

17:13.866 --> 17:16.117
Golden Gristle, here we come!

17:16.201 --> 17:17.869
[Gristle] Ladies and gentlemen,

17:17.953 --> 17:20.622
The West Bergen Town Pet Show
is under way!

17:20.705 --> 17:22.624
Round one tests form--

17:22.708 --> 17:27.880
regal bearing, shiny coat,
and, most importantly, strong butts.

17:27.963 --> 17:31.425
-[applause]
-[humming]

17:32.760 --> 17:34.720
Hmm, what have we here?

17:37.014 --> 17:38.474
Very confident!

17:38.557 --> 17:41.518
[cheers and applause]

17:41.602 --> 17:43.270
Round two tests posing.

17:43.353 --> 17:46.648
Which pet has the look that makes us feel
like dirt in its presence?

17:46.732 --> 17:49.401
[brassy music]

17:49.485 --> 17:51.820
♪ ♪

17:51.904 --> 17:53.322
No.

17:53.405 --> 17:55.199
♪ ♪

17:55.282 --> 17:57.701
-[camera shutter clicking]
-[yawns] Kill me.

17:57.785 --> 17:58.994
♪ ♪

17:59.078 --> 18:00.746
Hold the phone!

18:00.829 --> 18:01.914
♪ ♪

18:01.997 --> 18:03.165
[camera shutter clicking]

18:03.248 --> 18:06.627
It's like he sees my very soul, and...

18:06.710 --> 18:09.046
and he's not impressed!

18:09.129 --> 18:11.090
-Perfect score!
-[cheers and applause]

18:11.173 --> 18:13.634
You were sensational, Mr. Dinkles!

18:13.717 --> 18:15.302
Whoo, yeah!

18:15.385 --> 18:18.097
All you have to do now is score well
in the talent round,

18:18.180 --> 18:20.182
and you're a lock for "Best In Show"!

18:21.100 --> 18:23.477
[gasps] Ew.

18:25.646 --> 18:28.065
[grunting]

18:28.148 --> 18:32.319
Biggie, is it just me, or is Dinkles,
like, bird-level full of himself?

18:32.402 --> 18:36.824
Oh. No, no, I'm sure he's just tired
from the long day.

18:36.907 --> 18:38.367
Pardon me.

18:38.450 --> 18:41.662
It was a true honor
to compete against your pet.

18:41.745 --> 18:44.665
Would he mind giving us an autograph?

18:44.748 --> 18:47.835
Well, of course.
He'd love to, wouldn't you, Mr. Dinkles?

18:47.918 --> 18:49.336
-Meep.
-[squawks]

18:49.419 --> 18:52.923
[gasps] Don't say that!
He has a very pretty face.

18:53.006 --> 18:55.551
And I'm sure his mother is lovely.

18:55.634 --> 18:58.262
-[squawks]
-Sebastian, no!

18:58.345 --> 19:00.055
Don't go to your dark place again!

19:00.139 --> 19:01.974
That pet of yours is an animal!

19:02.057 --> 19:03.976
An animal!

19:04.059 --> 19:05.561
What has gotten into you?

19:05.644 --> 19:07.437
It's not his fault, Biggie.

19:07.521 --> 19:11.316
Nangus's training is making him think
he's better than everyone.

19:11.400 --> 19:12.442
Wrong again, Branch.

19:12.526 --> 19:16.572
It's Nangus's training that's making him
think he's better than everyone.

19:16.655 --> 19:17.906
Okay, that's what I just said.

19:17.990 --> 19:21.243
We have to find Nangus and see if
he can reverse this before it's too late.

19:21.326 --> 19:24.079
You mean... drop out of the contest?

19:24.163 --> 19:27.207
But if Mr. Dinkles doesn't win
the Golden Gristle...

19:27.291 --> 19:28.375
[thunder booming]

19:28.458 --> 19:31.003
[all booing]

19:31.086 --> 19:33.297
[Gristle]
In a disappointing turn of events,

19:33.380 --> 19:37.301
Mr. Dinkles forfeited the final event
and lost the Golden Gristle!

19:37.384 --> 19:38.719
[thunder booming]

19:40.304 --> 19:42.389
You didn't stand by me, Biggie,

19:42.472 --> 19:46.018
and now my self-esteem is lost forever.

19:46.101 --> 19:51.857
No!

19:53.317 --> 19:54.151
Huh?

19:54.234 --> 19:57.196
[Gristle] All finalists report
to the show floor for the talent event.

19:57.279 --> 19:58.864
Let's go, Mr. Dinkles.

20:00.282 --> 20:01.575
But, Biggie...

20:01.658 --> 20:03.035
Sorry.

20:03.118 --> 20:05.162
He needs that trophy.

20:05.245 --> 20:08.582
[accordion music]

20:08.665 --> 20:10.626
I can't decide
what this makes me feel more--

20:10.709 --> 20:12.836
irritation or boredom.

20:12.920 --> 20:14.004
It's boredom.

20:15.130 --> 20:16.423
You're next, Mr. Dinkles.

20:16.506 --> 20:19.843
This is going to be your finest moment.
I'm sure of it.

20:19.927 --> 20:21.762
[Bernice] I don't understand.

20:21.845 --> 20:23.513
What's wrong, Num-nums?

20:23.597 --> 20:25.015
[growls]

20:25.098 --> 20:27.893
Why? Why do you treat me like this?

20:27.976 --> 20:32.606
You used to be so sweet...
before you won that Golden Gristle.

20:32.689 --> 20:34.107
Remember her?

20:34.191 --> 20:36.276
I want this Num-nums back!

20:37.152 --> 20:40.656
[crying] Num-nums!

20:40.739 --> 20:42.115
How awful.

20:42.199 --> 20:45.452
We could never end up like that,
could we, Mr. Dinkles?

20:45.535 --> 20:48.372
-Mr. Dinkles?
-[Gristle] Next up, Mr. Dinkles!

20:48.455 --> 20:51.458
-[crowd] Dinkles, Dinkles, Dinkles...
-[Gristle] This is it!

20:51.541 --> 20:54.461
If he wins the Golden Gristle,
his life changes forever...

20:54.544 --> 20:56.171
[echoing] ...forever, forever.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.423
Wait! Mr. Dinkles, no!

20:58.507 --> 21:02.010
[energetic music]

21:02.094 --> 21:03.011
[crowd gasps]

21:03.095 --> 21:07.766
Sorry, but we need to go undo
your training right now.

21:07.849 --> 21:08.850
[crowd jeering]

21:08.934 --> 21:11.186
Forget the trophy. We don't need it.

21:12.104 --> 21:13.897
Let Dinkles do his thing!

21:13.981 --> 21:15.023
Meep.

21:15.107 --> 21:18.735
[gasps]
Where on Earth did you learn that word?

21:18.819 --> 21:22.572
-Come on, get on with it!
-Amuse us!

21:22.656 --> 21:23.865
[jeering continues]

21:23.949 --> 21:28.161
Fine. If you won't go with me,
you leave me only one choice.

21:28.245 --> 21:29.913
Five, six, seven, eight!

21:29.997 --> 21:34.001
Come on, Mr. D,
snap out of it and shake that thing!

21:34.084 --> 21:35.961
Get off the stage!

21:36.044 --> 21:38.005
Come on, we've got to help him.

21:39.798 --> 21:41.174
Come on, Mr. Dinkles.

21:41.258 --> 21:43.719
Yeah, meep, meep, Mr. Dinkles.

21:45.220 --> 21:47.139
Please, Mr. D!

21:47.222 --> 21:49.141
This is who you really are.

21:49.224 --> 21:51.601
This is who you really are!

21:51.685 --> 21:55.939
This is who you really are!

21:56.023 --> 21:57.816
-[bell dings]
-Meep.

21:59.568 --> 22:03.071
[Biggie] Yay!

22:03.155 --> 22:05.824
[booing]

22:05.907 --> 22:08.160
This is the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen

22:08.243 --> 22:09.911
in all my year of commentating!

22:09.995 --> 22:12.122
So many feels.

22:12.205 --> 22:15.208
[upbeat accordion music]

22:15.292 --> 22:16.877
♪ ♪

22:16.960 --> 22:21.006
And the winner
of the Golden Gristle is Num-nums.

22:21.089 --> 22:23.175
[cheering]

22:23.258 --> 22:25.469
Sorry Dinkles didn't win, Biggie.

22:25.552 --> 22:26.553
Oh, that's okay.

22:26.636 --> 22:28.847
I think I learned
an important lesson today,

22:28.930 --> 22:30.557
a lesson about...

22:30.640 --> 22:32.350
Well, it's, um...

22:32.434 --> 22:33.977
Meep.

22:34.061 --> 22:36.563
Poetically said, Mr. D.

22:36.646 --> 22:40.442
That is the perfect way to sum it all up.

22:42.360 --> 22:45.697
